\n<Manu><WordWrap>CHEF, what's going on here exactly?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Who are you even...?
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Manu...
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Just...Why...Why all of this. Is this some ploy to mock me for failing?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>And whats does this all mean CHEF?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Why did you bring me here?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>And whats does this all mean CHEF?
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Manu, the reason to why I wanted you to come here in the Capitol is to tell you th truth...
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Truth about what?
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>The reason why I brought here in the first place, is that you have lost your way of cooking.

\n<CHEF><WordWrap>You had a dream that could be achieved so easily, but you have caught up with your delusion that you think you could become the best culinary chef by just making fancy food for the people.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>But in truth, you had lost yourself the minute you decided to cook blindly on your path to becomming a chef.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>You chase what's the best new gimmick in cooking that has blinded you in to thinking that would get you a culinary status. But you failed hard...
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>That's when I decided to help you Manu...You were a man full of ambition, and I did not want you to loose that ambition over some failures and dissapointments.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>That's why I brought you here to Gastropolis. To teach you to cook and to learn your mistakes, as well as the value of culture that has molded the foods here in Gastropolis.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Now, do you understand the purpose of this entire whole ordeal?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Then why did you kept me from the dark and was this whole thing stagged from the beginning?
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Well If I had told you the true purpose of this whole ordeal, you would think that you were too good to enter anyway...
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>And not all of it was stagged, especially Esbeche's. He literally made a problem to this contest...But that's for later.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>But I still don't get it why even go that far to set this whole thing up?
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>It wouldn't be a contest if it were that short. Am I right?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>True...Now what now?
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Now?...We have a cooking contest of course.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Wait, WHAT!
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>You heard me. We'll have a last cook off inside the Capitol building.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>There will be a timer for 15 minutes. If you fail making the dishes and serving them on the table then its an automatic loose to you Manu.
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Ok then, what's the dishes we are going to make then?
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Well since you were able to help Paz, Esbeche, and Oggay, I think the best dishes to make is Batchoy, Kinilaw, and Cassava Cake.
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>So, are you up for the challenge Manu?
\n<Manu><WordWrap>Your on CHEF!
\n<CHEF><WordWrap>Great, now follow me.
